properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 12 at 4:51PM PST until January 13 at 12:00PM PST by NWS Spokane WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...North winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 50 mph. Wind
chill readings dropping to -10F to 0F overnight and Monday
morning.

* WHERE...Okanogan Valley.

* WHEN...Until noon PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Very windy conditions will develop between
6 PM and 8 PM this evening. Windy conditions will persist into
Monday morning.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON PST MONDAY
